John D. NAGLE, as Commissioner of Immigration for the Port of San Francisco, California, Appellant, v. Silvio ROSET, Appellee. No. 6258. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 1, 1931. Geo. J. Hatfield, U. S. Atty., of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Alfred L. Branch, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for the respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that -the order of the District Court in. this cause be, and hereby is, reversed.
